@node WARRANTY "Warranty ?"

   @{u}Warranty declaration:@{uu}

     THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED  "AS-IS"  AND  SUBJECT  TO  CHANGE.  NO
     WARRANTIES  ARE  MADE. YOU USE THIS SOFTWARE AT YOUR OWN RISK. NO
     RELIABILITY OR RESPONSIBILITY IS ASSUMED.

     Dortmund, Germany, 30. Juni 1997

     Christoph Dahlen

     @{b}In other words: If this piece of software will acidently  execute
     the command c:delete sys:#? all force, it's your fault :)@{ub}

     But serious, this skript has undergone extensive  testing  and  I
     found  out  that  it  only  will  do, what it is intended for. It
     contains no direct  file  manipulation  commands  in  it  and  no
     backdoor. No secrets mails with your password will be send.

     Anyway, I advise you not to let  this  script  work  without  any
     surveilance,  because  doing a exchange via a (paid) phoneline is
     allways risky. This script is designed  to  reset  Miami  to  its
     prior  state,  when  an error or a user break occured. So it will
     drop the line if Miami was offline at startup.  Or  at  least  @{b}it
     should!@{ub}

@endnode
@node INSTALL "Installation"

   @{u}Installation guide@{uu}

     Installation is very simple, just move this script to a directory
     you  like.  You should optain that this script has no path to the
     needed softwaretools set, so is should either reside in the  same
     directory as the tools do, or the tools should be in the standard
     AmigaDOS search path:

     > copy UMSXChange.good UMS:Rexx

     If you want to start this script from a shell  window  but  don't
     like  the  ARexx  "RX"  prefix, just make this script executable.
     This is done via AmigaDOS' "protect" command:

     > protect UMSXChange.good +s

     Here is a example line from ums.config how to add  UMSXChange  in
     your GoodNews ARexx Menu:

     ( GoodNews.RexxMenu
         "#? \"ums:rexx/UMSXChange.good \"UMSXChange\" \n"
          )

     That's all, folks.

@endnode
@node CONFIG "Configuration"

   @{u}Firsttime Configuration@{uu}

     If you start this script for the first  time,  GoodNews  must  be
     running,   because  it's  ARexx  GUI  access  will  be  used  for
     requesters and similar. If GoodNews is not running  you  will  be
     presented a error message.

     The configuration sequence will ask you for the following things:

     · Where to find MIAMI
     · Name of your NNTP newsserver
     · Wether your NNTP server is capable of the NEWNEWS command
     ·· To be honest, I don't know much about the NNTP protokoll,
        the NEWNEWS parameter will change the call for umsnntpget.
        With NEWNEWS = YES it will be "umsnntpget -h<HOST>", with
        NEWNEWS = NO it will be "umsnntpget -g -h<HOST>".
     · Name of your SMTP mailsserver
     · Name of your POP3 mailserver
     · Your POP3 Login account
     · Your POP3 Login password
     · Wether to use SetFolder and depending on the answer
     ·· The UMSName for SetFolder. By now, it must be a name with
        no password!

     @{b}All your answers will  be  stored  in  ENVARC:UMSXChange,  so  be
     warned:  Your  POP3  password  is  contained there in a uncrypted
     format.@{ub}

     For a reconfiguration delete this prefs-file and re-start
     UMSXChange

    @{u}Debugging@{uu}

     If you want to trace the program enter the following lines in a
     shell:

     > setenv UMSXChange.debug "YES"
     > tco

     For stopping the debugging process enter the line below:

     > unsetenv UMSXChange.debug
     > tcc

@endnode
@node USAGE "Usage"

   @{u}Program Usage@{uu}

     Programm usage is as simple as the @{"installation" link INSTALL}. You can use this
     script in two modes:

     1.) With GoodNews running, you will be asked wether to  get  news
     @{b}or@{ub} mail @{b}or@{ub} both. After the exchange is done GoodNews will be sent
     a "Rescan All". Depending on your configuration "SetFolder"  will
     be called in advance.

     2.) Without GoodNews running  news  @{b}and@{ub}  mail  will  be  fetched.
     Depending on your configuration "SetFolder" will be called.

     After being started UMSXChange will start  Miami  if  it  is  not
     allready  running,  and  let  it  go  online  if  it isn't. After
     connections  is  established  UMSXChange   will   exchange   your
     messages.

     @{b}If selected@{ub} it first send your mails to the SMTP  host  and  gets
     the new one from your POP3 account.

     @{b}If selected@{ub} it second sends your articles to the  NNTP  host  and
     gets the new arrived from the server.

     After all the exchange is done, UMSXChange will  reset  Miami  to
     the status it had before the script was started.

     @{b}If selected@{ub} in the configuration "SetFolder" will be  called  and
     afterwards, if GoodNews' ARexx port is found, it will be asked to
     do a "Rescan All"

     If at runtime a error occurs UMSXChange will  instantly  jump  to
     the "Reset-Miami-Section".

     Note: UMSXChange can have no influence on the external tools,  so
     if  nntpget  freezes  the  skript  will  not  continue  and  your
     phoneline will not be cut! See also section "@{"Warranty" link WARRANTY}"

@endnode
